# UC IPM Pest Notes: Cockroaches (7467)
Source: UC Statewide Integrated Pest Management Program, Revised December 2019

## Page 1

Pest Notes, Publication 7467
Integrated Pest Management In and Around Buildings
There are five species of cockroaches in 
California that are commonly regarded 
as pests: German cockroach, brown-
banded cockroach, oriental cockroach, 
American cockroach, and Turkestan 
cockroach. 
People are repulsed when they find 
cockroaches in their homes and other 
buildings. Indoor infestations of cock-
roaches are also important sources of 
allergens and have been identified as 
risk factors for development of asthma 
in children, especially within multi-
unit housing environments. The levels 
of allergens present have been directly 
