# SF.gov — Pay your annual healthy housing fee for apartment buildings

- **Original URL:** https://www.sf.gov/pay-your-annual-healthy-housing-fee-apartment-buildings
- **Source title:** Pay your annual healthy housing fee for apartment buildings
- **Authority:** SF.gov / SFDPH Environmental Health
- **Export date:** 2026-07-02
- **Format:** md (web extract)
- **Reviewer:** CA
- **Phase used:** Phase 1 (`payFee`, `pestsTopic` fee card)

---

## Who must pay

You need to pay this annual fee if you own an apartment building with **3 or more rental units**.

## Fee amount

Check your invoice for the exact amount. The number of rental units you have determines your fee.

## Billing and exemption

We will mail you an invoice every year for this healthy housing fee.

The number of rental units you have determines your fee. If you have **less than 3 rented units during the year**, you do not need to pay this fee. If you have 3 or more rented units, pay the fee using one of the methods described below.

## Payment methods

- Pay online
- Pay in-person with a check, cash, or money order at City Hall, Room 1401, Dr. Carlton B. Goodlett Place, San Francisco, CA 94102
- Pay by mail: write a check or money order to the "Department of Public Health", include your invoice number, and mail to P.O. BOX 7429, San Francisco, CA 94120

## Owner-occupied buildings

If you own and live in your apartment building:

- If you rent **less than 3 units during the year**, you do not need to pay the fee.
- If you rent **3 or more units during the year**, you still need to pay the fee.
- Include the total number of rental units and the number of owner-occupied units on your invoice. You must sign and date the certification statement at the bottom of the bill and send it back to us.
- You will still get an invoice each year for your records.

## Late penalties

If you are late, you will also need to pay a late fee:

- $10 within 30 days of the due date
- $30 within 60 days of the due date

We will also apply an interest rate of 1.5% per month and place a lien on your property.

## Contact

- Phone: 415-252-3800
- Email: healthyhousing@sfdph.org

## Mockup fields covered

- `payFee` — summary, who must pay, exemption, payment routes, help contact
- `pestsTopic` — `sections[3].cards[2].text` (fee card routing)

## Does not cover

- Certified dollar amounts by rental-unit tier (see EHB fee schedule and Controller fee certification extracts)
