# SFDPH Environmental Health Branch — Fee Schedule (rates effective 7/1/25–6/30/26)

- **Original URL:** https://media.api.sf.gov/documents/Website_Fees_FY25-26_1M8m5aT.pdf
- **Source title:** Department of Public Health - Environmental Health Branch — Fee Schedule, Application, License, and Other Fees
- **Authority:** SFDPH Environmental Health Branch (Controller-adjusted fees under Health Code Sec. 609.2)
- **Export date:** 2026-07-06
- **Format:** md (PDF extract)
- **Reviewer:** CA
- **Phase used:** Current source of truth for `payFee` and `noticeOfViolation` fee figures, superseding the FY 2024–25 estimate and the Aug 2025 Controller certification pre-round.

---

## Healthy Housing Program — Apartment Buildings (rates effective 7/1/25–6/30/26, revised 7/3/2025)

| Number of rental units | Fee per building per year |
| --- | --- |
| 3 | $101 |
| 4–6 | $127 |
| 7–10 | $171 |
| 11–15 | $343 |
| 16–20 | $475 |
| 21–30 | $673 |
| Over 30 | $791 |

## Healthy Housing reinspection fees

- Reinspection by environmental health inspector, per hour: $251
- Reinspection by environmental health technician, per hour: $229
- Additional fee for reinspections requiring more than one hour — each additional half hour: $125 (inspector) / $113 (technician)

## Late payment penalty

- $10 after 30 days
- $30 after 60 days
- Interest accrues at 1.5% per month from date of recordation (Refuse Lien Program rate; applied citywide by EHB to unpaid balances)

## Note for mockup copy

This document has rates effective through June 30, 2026, and was the most recently published EHB fee schedule as of this export (2026-07-06 — six days into FY 2026–27). No FY 2026–27 schedule was found published at export time; re-verify against a newer certification before publishing. SF.gov's live `payFee` transaction page still directs owners to **check their invoice** for the exact amount rather than publishing a table — Transaction pages also do not support a table block in Karl CMS (see `docs/karl-help-center-research-2026-07-06.md`), so any published fee tiers must live in prose/bullets on Transaction/Information pages or in a table on a Resource Collection's linked document, not as a hardcoded page-level table.

## Corrects

- `notebooklm/hhvc-standards-manual.md` Chapter 8.2 and `pages/pay-healthy-housing-fee.js` previously published a table ($103/$129/$174/$350/$485/$688/$808 apartment-building tiers and $256/$234 hourly rates) that this document's export (2026-07-06) flagged as "unsourced" because no FY 2026-27 schedule had been found published at that time.

## Superseded (2026-07-06, same day)

