### **4.3 Content Type Selection Matrix**

To ensure that all pages are consistently organized around user tasks, editors must use the following **Content Type Selection Matrix** [218, 243]. To maintain search engine findability and prevent layout errors, never guess a page type; map the primary resident goal directly to its approved Karl content type [240, 243, 246]:

| **Resident Goal or Action**                              |  **Karl Content Type**  | **HHVC Program Example**                         |
| :------------------------------------------------------- | :---------------------: | :----------------------------------------------- |
| File a cockroach, mold, or bed bug report online         |     **Transaction**     | _Report cockroaches_ [246]                       |
| Pay an annual apartment program fee or late fee          |     **Transaction**     | _Pay your Healthy Housing fee_ [246]             |
| Learn how to seal cracks to keep mice out of a kitchen   |     **Information**     | _Keep rats and mice out_ [246]                   |
| Understand what steps to take after filing a complaint   |    **Step-by-step**     | _What happens after you report_ [246]            |
| Prepare a unit for an upcoming SRO hygiene inspection    |    **Step-by-step**     | _Get ready for an SRO inspection_ [246]          |
| Review legal requirements of a Notice of Violation (NOV) |     **Information**     | _Understand a notice of violation_ [246]         |
| Find and download the landlord Bed Bug Disclosure form   | **Resource Collection** | _Vermin prevention guides and forms_ [246]       |
| View the program mission, office hours, and district map |        **About**        | _About Healthy Housing and Vector Control_ [246] |

